title: Solstice Surrender by Tracy Cooper-Posey
description:
A man of mysterious powers. A woman who fights her destiny.
On mid-winter's eve she must decide. When her SIA partner
and lover is killed on assignment, Jenna hides away in Banff,
Canada for the Christmas season to lick her wounds in private.
When she forces a rude stranger to dump coffee in his own lap
just by thinking about it, Jenna is tipped into a shadowy
world hidden to most humans. Rhys Cellyn knows that dangerous,
powerful world intimately. He helps Jenna avoid the many
enemies who now want her for her fast-developing powers, while
Jenna struggles to accept the truth about her true fate, her
growing feelings for Rhys and their twined destinies.

Time is against her, for she must make a choice and the future
of the world is at stake...if she can only keep Rhys and herself
alive until the moment of the winter solstice.

Solstice Surrender
by Tracy Cooper-Posey
